Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveTop basketballer, Lebron James has become the first NBA player to hit billionaire status while still playing.
According to Forbes, the basketballer became a billionaire after another “monster year of earnings, totaling $121.2 million last year.”
The 37-year-old superstar has a net worth of $1 billion. The magazine claim he is the first active NBA player to make the billionaires list. Michael Jordan, the only other basketball billionaire, didn’t hit become one until 2014, more than a decade after he retired.
